<dl id="n08131i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08131i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08131i"> 131(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> majority votes for slavery</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Review by G.O&apos;B. <font color="green">[George O&apos;Brien]</font> of <i>The Referendum</i>, by J. St. Loe Strachey (T. Fisher Unwin. 3/6 net): Mr Strachey &hellip; tells us that &ldquo;if a <mark>majority of the people were to introduce slavery</mark> into this country, I should hold that the right to resistance even to a majority had arisen.&rdquo; <small> <a name="IS2feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IS2feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (2 February 1924) 662b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
